TODO:Enemy surprise has been adjusted. It is now a fixed 15% chance. In addition to delaying enemy actions, it now applies a 1 tn {colour_start|move}Stumble{colour_end}, and reduces enemy accuracy by another 50% . 

{colour_start|notable}This makes moves that would normally perform during the Prep Round have a 50% less chance of hitting, while other moves have their accuracy reduced to the 5% hit minimum.{colour_end}

Certain enemy factions, specifically those found in low light are immune to being surprised.

TODO:Certain Troglodyte enemies have a special {colour_start|notable}Swarm{colour_end} typing.

If left alone for too long, these meek Trogs will call for reinforcements, bringing a similar ally to their side, {colour_start|notable}doubling its total HP, and granting the unit a second action.{colour_end}

Stamping out these pests as quickly as possible can keep the fight under control.

